text: Enjoy the weekend to my lovers, haters and those that just dont give a damn. Be safe.

@realmoney Buy Banks, Short Bonds? I remain very optimistic regarding the intermediate term outlook for bank stocks. Given Powell's comments yesterday combined with the vast underperformance in 2020, it might now finally be time for the banks to move out of their recent trading

ranges. Also favoring financials could be a further flattening of the Covid-19 curve, continued therapeutic and vaccination hopes, yield curve normalization (and higher long term bond yields) and signs of a steady (but still tepid) domestic economic recovery. Furthermore, any
rotation out of FAANG + MSFT might need to find a home - and bank stocks, with their historically low relative valuations - might be such a place.

Given how much money is positioned in the anointed stocks, it woudn't take too much of a rotation out of FB, AMZN, AAPL et al to move the poorly regarded bank equities. @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @riskreversal @ScottWapnerCNBC @andrewrsorkin @saraeisen
